=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/utrippiest1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trippiest1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#871F78>(4/5/02 3:43:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=994.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: PvP Thread</span><hr size=1> Went to the arena the other night for some guild fun.  I fought three classes: 40 magician, 42 SK, and 41 wizard.  I was level 39.  Btw, I am an Ogre.  I beat the snot out of all three classes, wizard actually being the most difficult of the three.  Tactics were basically centered around the Blitzkrieg concept: hit them fast and hard and with everything you've got and do not let up for a second.  The minute you hesitate or stop to think, it's over.  But here's a play-by-play:<br><br>Magician:<br>As soon as the word was given to begin... immediately sic'ed pet on the mage.  Of course his earth pet ran out and tried to root him.  The root failed a couple times but that didn't matter because his pet now had mine's attention... no matter.  I closed in on the high-elf and decended upon him with a flurry from my hammer and baton (11/20 and 8/20 with SCHW haste).  Meanwhile he was attempting to cast his first nuke.  I interrupted him.  While waiting for Slam to recharge, I FoL'ed him.  FoL is absolutely KEY to duels.  I guess the mage was inexperienced in this regard 'cause he was absolutely defenseless after I blinded him: he just sat there and casted nothing.  So while he was blind, I proceeded to beat the poop out of him and the pet fighting continued.  The mage pet was winning, but not by much.  Mind you, this is about 4 seconds into the fight, so the amount of damage the pets did to each other was of no concern at this point.  Continued beating on the mage while ensuring that FoL stayed on him; i.e. recast.  Also kept Slamming him regardless of whether or not he was casting, since he was blind... wanted to keep him from running around aimlessly if he decided and realized he could run.  So about 10 to 15 seconds into the fight, the mage had not gotten even one nuke to cast, much less land.  My pet was down to about 45% or so, his 60%.  Not a prob, though.  I re-blinded the poor mage and combined that with another slam that landed, thereby stunning him.  Took a second to cast Yeshan's Recovery to heal the pet to full and then resumed my onslaught on the helpless mage.  FoL wore off and he started running around immediately but he was down to about 30% hps.  I followed him and had no problem continuing my staying right on top of him given that I was sow'ed and he was not.  At this point the mage started to panic... he stopped to cast one of his faster, less-damaging nukes.  Slam missed this time and his nuke landed for approximately 100pts or so.  Big deal.  Now he was down to about 20%.  FYI, here is a bit of info. you all might find useful.  In general, when an enemy target that has hit you gets down to 20% or less hps, your pet will immediately switch focus to him to help finish him off - even if he is on another target - much like NPCs do.  So, the bloodlusting pet detecting that the mage was about to die immediately pulled himself off the mage pet and closed in the pathetic high-elf.  The mage pet meanwhile kept attacking my pet and attempted to root him... it failed.  The fight lasted about another 3 seconds after that.  In total, the fight lasted maybe 25 seconds.<br><br>Duel number 2 - SK using 2hs:<br>This was a pretty boring fight too, actually.  When the word was given I opened with the same tactic - immediately sent pet in and blitzkrieg'ed the enemy.  The SK opened with Fear.  But I got to him before he finished casting.  Slam missed but pet interrupted him.  I FoL'ed him immediately but he had already started melee so benefitted by being able to swing while blind.  Not a problem though.  I simply moved around behind him and attacked his back while he was blind, all the while the pet's mauling him from the front.  FoL wore off fairly quickly though.  Recast it... failed to stick.  SK turned around and again begins to cast Fear.  Slam wasn't up yet and pet had used up his bash too.  So I tried FoL again... failed.  He noticed an opportunity here and began to cast Fear again.  It landed this time.  I ran away while pet continued to hammer on him.  At this point, I had only taken about 20% of his hps.  He began to cast Engulfing Darkness (everyone recognized that distinct sound).  I resisted.  He tried again but pet must have interrupted him cause I did not see a resist message and nothing landed on me, of course.  Fear wore off.  I instantly started casting FoL.  It landed.  While running back toward him I considered slowing him but that would have been a waste of a couple seconds since he was already swinging slowly with a 2hs.  At this point, I was still at full hps.  He was down to about 60% - pet was chewing him up this whole time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    .  I positioned myself behind him again and started unloading my hammer/baton blows to his back.  FoL lasted about 3 seconds but enough to knock him down to 45% hps.  FoL wore off and he did not hesitate to HT me at that point.  It did 300 pts of dmg or so to me if I remember correctly.  Took me down to about 75% hps.  He swung around.  I started casting FoL... resisted.  He landed a hit... for approx 40 pts or so.  He bagan casting Fear again.  Slammed him and interrupted him again.  FoL'ed him and it stuck.  Ran around to his back.  SK got smart and tried to approximate where I would be while blind.  He only slightly miscalculated... np, moved again to his back but then decided I had a little room to play with so I backed away a bit and cast a heal.  Recast FoL.  It landed, thereby renewing blindness.  Cast another quick heal on myself and I was back up to a little more than 90% hps.  Checked pets hps and noticed the SK took him down to only about 90% hps.  Pet was doing fine.  Recast FoL again but he resisted, however blindness was still in effect.  Started casting Spirit Strike... fizzle, fizzle, started casting succesfully.  At this point he was down to about 20% and going down pretty fast.  Blindess wore off.  He foolishly took the time to spin around to look for me.  Didn't start casting Fear until then.  Spirit Strike landed a micro-second later and I of course darted in to attempt to interrupt him.  Slam landed and I interrupted his casting.  He was down to about 15% now while I was at approx 90%.  At that point I just decided to remain and finish him off... figured I could afford him landing a Fear since he was so low.  We traded blows for another 5 seconds or so before he fell.  Pet was at full hps and I was at 80% or so.<br><br>Wizard:<br>As usual, sent pet in immediately.  Wizard took the bait and took the time to root the pet.  I closed in and began swinging.  Took a couple swings and then started casting FoL... landed.  Continued swinging but I was doing no damage.  I was only a little worried at that point.  She had been blinded before, evidently, because she began casting a nuke.  I hadn't used Slam yet... successfully interrupted her.  Pet root was still holding.  Then her dmg-absorbing shield dropped.  AH HA!  Started recasting FoL and she started root.  FoL wore off.  Shortly after I finished casting FoL, which did not land, her root landed.  I'd taken only 10% of her hps away at that point.  Pet was still rooted.  She stepped back a bit and began casting a nuke.  A half-second later her root wore off, the one on my sow'ed pet.  So pet lunged at her and conveniently interrupted her.  My root was still holding.  No chance to pummel her face in so I decided to try EB.  She started casting a nuke again and it landed.  OUCH!  Quick 250 hps knocked off.  I finished casting EB on her and it landed.  Being rooted, I was not about to stop my onslaught so I started casting Spirit Strike.  She started casting another nuke.  Spirt Strike hit and hurt her a little, but not too badly so I decided to give her another.  Pet interrupted her casting, evidently.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Second &quot;nuke&quot; of mine landed.  She tried to root my pet.  Not sure if it landed or not.  Figuring that my root would be wearing off soon, I began preparing for my assault by casting FoL... resisted.  Casted again... resisted.  She started casting again (a nuke) and so did I (FoL).  FoL finsished and landed before she finished her nuke.  OUCH!  Another 278 pts or so gone.  But she started running around ( root landed on pet).  I was down to about 55 to 60% or so but so was she... actually closer to 50% or less.  My root wore off and I rushed her, trying to get behind her.  She stopped and started casting.  She was at about 35 to 40% hps now.  I took a couple swings at her back and landed a slam to interrupt her before FoL wore off.  At the same time, pet's root wore off.  After that, the fight lasted maybe 4 more seconds before we'd beaten the poop out of her.  Was a very fun fight.  Altogether it lasted probably about 45 to 60 seconds, which seems like a lifetime during a duel.<br><br>The cool thing was that nobody in the guild that was a similar level wanted to fight me after that.  Heh. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/utrippiest1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trippiest1</A> at: 4/5/02 3:46:33 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/u